::Feline::

She turns and looks at Zardus. "Yes, that is correct.  As far as I 
know, they don't even know I exist yet."


--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, Yanshosh@a... wrote:
> Skulletron hasn't posted the whole day yesterday, so I'll just 
begin.
> 
> ::Zardus::
> 
> Zardus walks into the conference room, looking at the mechfluid 
stains from 
> the recent massacure.
> 
> "You'll have to exuse the mechfluid," he says to the other 
two, "Things get 
> out of hand occasionally."
> 
> He walks over to the holo-projectors, tapping a few buttons. A 
hologram of 
> the Cybertronian Fire appears on the table.
> 
> "Recently, the Maximals got a new base," he says, pointing at the 
hologram, 
> "They have some sort of jamming system set up, our scanners cannot 
get 
> through to the inside."
> 
> He looks at the two. "You are new to this planet, the Maximals 
wouldn't know 
> that you are Alliance members. Is that correct?" he asks, studying 
Feline and 
> Skulletron carefully.
